    <main>
        <section class="introduction">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Welcome to CodePoker Quest, a thrilling fusion of poker strategy and coding challenges. Immerse yourself in a unique gaming experience that combines the excitement of poker gameplay with the creativity of coding. Get ready for an adventure where every hand you play is a step closer to mastering the CodePoker universe.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>How to Play</h2>
            <p>Your goal is to reach a specified number of points by skillfully playing poker hands. Follow these steps to navigate through the game:</p>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Starting a Level:</strong> Each level begins with a set number of points to reach. You are dealt a standard poker hand.</li>
                <li><strong>Building Hands:</strong> Use your poker skills to create the best possible hand from the cards dealt. The strength of your hand determines the points earned.</li>
                <li><strong>Reaching the Target:</strong> Play multiple hands to accumulate points. Keep an eye on the target points for the level.</li>
                <li><strong>Bonus Card Prompt:</strong> Upon reaching the target, describe a bonus card. The more creative and strategic your description, the more bonus points you can earn.</li>
                <li><strong>OpenAPI Code Generation:</strong> Your bonus card description triggers a request to the OpenAPI chatGPT API, generating code for the bonus card.</li>
                <li><strong>Applying Bonus Card:</strong> Implement the generated code in your game to activate the bonus card, gaining unique advantages for extra points.</li>
                <li><strong>Advancing to the Next Level:</strong> Successfully using the bonus card adds to your total points. Move on to the next level and face new challenges.</li>
                <li><strong>Records Page:</strong> Your score will be saved even if you lose. Check your own and others' scores on the Records page for friendly competition and bragging rights!</li>
            </ol>
            <p>Explore the synergy of poker and coding, and may your hands be both lucky and skillful!</p>
        </section>
    </main>
